#Clean up the dataframe, remove columns that contains numbers
def RemoveCols(SomeDF):
    temp=SomeDF
    MyList = []
    for col in temp.columns:
        Logical2 = str.isalpha(col)
        if (Logical2==False):
         MyList.append(str(col))
    temp.drop(MyList, axis=1,inplace=True)
    return temp

MyDF1 = RemoveCols(MyDF1)

def display_topics(model, feature_names, no_top_words):
    for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(model.components_):
        print("Topic %d:" % (topic_idx))
        print(" ".join([feature_names[i]
                        for i in topic.argsort()[:-no_top_words - 1:-1]]))

no_top_words = 20

print("Top 3 Topics for Reviews in sample #1")
display_topics(lda_model1, ColumnNames1, no_top_words)

print("Top 3 Topics for Reviews in sample #2")
display_topics(lda_model2, ColumnNames2, no_top_words)

word_topic = np.array(lda_model1.components_)
#print(word_topic)
word_topic = word_topic.transpose()

num_top_words = 18
vocab_array = np.asarray(ColumnNames1)

#fontsize_base = 70 / np.max(word_topic) # font size for word with largest share in corpus
fontsize_base = 10

NUM_TOPICS = 3

for t in range(NUM_TOPICS):
    plt.subplot(1, NUM_TOPICS, t + 1)  # plot numbering starts with 1
    plt.ylim(0, num_top_words + 0.5)  # stretch the y-axis to accommodate the words
    plt.xticks([])  # remove x-axis markings ('ticks')
    plt.yticks([]) # remove y-axis markings ('ticks')
    plt.title('Topic #{}'.format(t))
    top_words_idx = np.argsort(word_topic[:,t])[::-1]  # descending order
    top_words_idx = top_words_idx[:num_top_words]
    top_words = vocab_array[top_words_idx]
    top_words_shares = word_topic[top_words_idx, t]
    for i, (word, share) in enumerate(zip(top_words, top_words_shares)):
        plt.text(0.01, num_top_words-i-0.5, word, fontsize=fontsize_base)
                 ##fontsize_base*share)

#plt.tight_layout()
#plt.show()
plt.savefig("TopicsVis-sample1.pdf")

#Clean up the dataframe, remove columns that contains numbers
def RemoveCols(SomeDF):
    temp=SomeDF
    MyList = []
    for col in temp.columns:
        Logical2 = str.isalpha(col)
        if (Logical2==False):
         MyList.append(str(col))
    temp.drop(MyList, axis=1,inplace=True)
    return temp

DFreviewgender = RemoveCols(DFreviewgender)
